The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Loose Change
                                                                                                                           6                                                                                        LOOSE CHANGE
                              
	 HDFC Standard Life has launched its online buying channel starting with three products  YoungStar Super Suvidha, Pension Super, and Endowment Super Suvidha. By buying these products online customers can get a discount of 40 per cent on the first and second year premium allocation charges. The company also plans to sell other products such as pure protection and single premium products through the online channel in the near future.                            
	 LIC Cards Services has launched a card protection plan for its credit card customers in partnership with CPP Assistance Services. CPP Card Protection is Indias first comprehensive card protection service. LIC credit card customers can now block all their lost or stolen cards on a single call to CPPs 24-hour helpline from anywhere in the world. The plan is unique because customers have the benefit of calling the helpline and report their cards as lost. This one call will ensure CPP notifies all cards as lost, without the customer having to call individual issuers.                            
	 The Union Bank of India has raised deposit rates by up to 0.50 per cent across various maturities with effect from April 5.                                                                                                                              
